summaries.short: Stuart has a night on the town in Long Beach; Wade tries to win back Marion; Jessica evaluates her life.
summaries.full: Stuart bonds with some construction guys, who invite him for a night out in Long Beach with promises of his meeting easy women. Jessica gives Wade advice on how to win back Marion after 30 days of no communication.

summaries.full: Stuart plans an epic pool party in hopes that Kimberly, a model he recently met, will attend. Jessica finds inspiration in a homeless 19-year-old named Heaven.

summaries.short: As Stuart hits the gay-club circuit with Jessica, Wade and Kives have fun in Stuart's apartment.
summaries.full: After learning that gay clubs are frequented by straight women, Stuart ditches Wade (who was coming over for movie night) to tag along with Jessica to a gay club. Jessica manages to get herself and Stuart invited to a dinner party. Back at Stuart's house, Wade is joined by Kives and they have a fun night of their own in Stuart's house.

summaries.short: Stuart (Stephen Merchant) enlists his roommate Jessica to prove to a visiting ex-girlfriend that she made a huge mistake by leaving him.
summaries.full: Determined to impress his visiting ex-girlfriend Trudy and prove that she made a mistake by leaving him, Stuart gets a Russian model to pose as his girlfriend for a double date. When she cancels at the last minute, Stuart convinces his roommate Jessica to accompany him--a ruse that takes them to a swanky, star-studded LA hills house party, and leads to an unexpected denouement.

summaries.short: Stuart asks out a yoga-studio employee; Glenn gets Jessica an audition; Wade institutes an emergency-alert system.
summaries.full: Stuart has an encouraging first date with a yoga-studio employee named Annie, but ends up becoming unhinged. Meanwhile, upset that her frenemy Amelia (Jenny Slate) got a major-film role, Jessica demands that her agent/squeeze Glenn score her an audition, pronto. After a slip in the shower, Wade institutes an emergency-alert system for his friends.
